[1] Netherlands: vaccination against BTV-1 contemplated
Date: Wed 17 Sep 2008
Source: Agrarisch Dagblad (The Netherlands) [in Dutch, trans. Mod.AS, edited]
<http://www.agd.nl/1060543/Nieuws/Artikel/LNV-overweegt-aanschaf-vaccin-blauwtong-serotype-1.htm>


Ministry of Agriculture considers purchase of bluetongue vaccine type 1
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Agriculture, Nature and Food Quality (NLV) is
considering the purchase of vaccine against bluetongue serotype 1
[BTV-1]. This serotype, which has been spreading northwards from
Spain and France, is a different variant of bluetongue than serotype
8, against which the Dutch livestock has been vaccinated.

"Preventive vaccination against BTV-1 is currently not allowed.
According to the European legislation, vaccination is allowed only
after a confirmed outbreak of the disease [in the relevant country];
only then, vaccination may be performed within the 150-km (93.2 mi)
zone around the outbreak," said a spokesman for the Ministry. This
regulation is currently being debated.

In France, there is already a zone where both serotypes 1 and 8 are present.

[Byline: Mariska Vermaas]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[The updated French situation can be seen on the map included in
France's presentation of 16 Sep 2008 at the SCFCAH meeting in
